Rating: 3
I halved the recipe for 2 people -- which still yields plenty of compound butter. Here's an idea: about an hour before dinner, drape a small bowl with plastic wrap, then combine the butter ingredients in it, and, once mixed, roll the butter in the plastic wrap into a log, and place in the fridge. Once hardened, you can slice coins of butter that present better than the "dollop." I followed other reviewers' suggestions and lightly dredged the fish in salted flour. Overall it was really tasty and quick, -- when I make it again I'll do it without the crust -- and I can't wait to try the butter on other things.

