This was really a magnificent dish - but I made a few modifications. First of all, I used Orange Roughy rather than Tilapia. Secondly, when I was done sauteeing the fish, there were lots of brown bits at the bottom of the pan, so I added a few more minced shallots, sauteed for 10 seconds, then deglazed with a dry white wine (I used a Mexican Semillon) and then after 10 more seconds or so, I added some more of the chili-lime butter so that I had something like a beurre-blanc. Then I poured that liquid over the fish and it was absolutely superb. I think the wine gave a nice tartness that the butter alone was missing. And I don't recommend flouring the fish since orange roughy has such a nice flavor on its own - why cover it up?

