Rating: 0
For those of you who are flaming the reviewer who said this could be served to vegetarians, you might want to do a little research the next time. There are 4 types of vegetarians: semi-vegetarians-those who do not eat red meat but consume poultry, seafood, and dairy products, and these people, myself included, would eat this recipe, pesco vegetarians-those who do not eat red meat or poultry, lacto-ovo vegetarians- those who do not eat red meat, poultry, or seafood, and vegans- those who eat absolutely no food that contains any animal product whatsoever. And an aside to the reviewer from Leeds, UK, perhaps in the UK you don't call people pesco-vegetarians, but in the US it is a term that is used by vegetarians, and *gasp* even by people in the medical field when they are assessing the type of diet people follow.

