Rating: 3
I cook lots of fish lots of different ways and never had any difficulty with 'sticking' before. Using this method, it stuck big-time! It stuck so badly that the fillets in the first batch ended up in about 15 pieces. So I cleaned out the skillet and regrouped. For the second batch, I added a good bit more oil and lightly dredged each piece in flour as someone suggested. (Thanks for the tip!) It was a huge improvement. Both the color and the taste were much, much more appetizing. At first, the butter seemed like a huge flop, too -- just a big, hard blob on top (even though it had been left out to reach room temp as directed). About halfway through dinner, though, the butter finally melted. At that point, this whole disappointing meal did a 180. Once it liquified, the butter 'sauce' was scrumptious!! Next time, I think I'll broil the fish, putting the butter on top for the last 3 or 4 min. of cooking time. This one definitely needs 'tweaking', but the lime butter has some real possibilities!

