I cooked one pound of tilapia for two, but made the whole amount of chile lime butter. I'm glad I did. We also put some on our plain steamed broccoli, and there's not much of the butter left. If anyone out there is making the whole 30 to 36 ounces of fish, I'd suggest a lot more of the butter compound which can be frozen if needed. One-half teaspoon of salt in the butter seemed too much to me considering the fillets are also salted, so I cut it back to 1/4 teaspoon. (Note the reviewer who had to drink a lot of water to get through the meal!) Also I left the seeds from the pepper out of my mix. For our tastes these two adjustments were just right. Delicious way to prepare tilapia, and probably other non-oily fish as well.

